  "texts": [
    "Step 2 Implementation stage.",
    "Across both retrospective and prospective harmonization, data scientists must first define which variables they wish to harmonize.",
    "To make this decision, they must consider both the ultimate goal of the data harmonization (e.g.",
    "to conduct a theory-driven approach in order to test relationships between a given set of variables or to conduct a data-driven approach in order to discover relationships between a broad set of variables 51), what data is available for harmonization, and the acceptable level of harmonization.",
    "Note, in some fields, the term \"DataSchema\" is increasingly used to refer to the core variables that are ultimately selected for harmonization 20, [79] [80] [81]."
  ],
